
[1]elutriation

   ELUTRIA'TION, n. The operation of pulverizing a solid substance, mixing
   it with water, and pouring off the liquid,while the foul or extraneous
   substances are floating, or after the coarser particles have subsided,
   and while the finer parts are suspended in the liquor.
